               <p>S. Sarjent. Yes; I saw him about nine o'clock in the morning on Friday the 9th of March; he was in bed, he seemed to be in a fit; I spoke to him several times, he made me no answer; I saw him twice that day; I saw him at nine o'clock at night, he was very bad then.</p>
               <p>Q. Had you any doubt but he was really ill?</p>
               <p>S. Sarjent. No; I saw him about two o'clock on Saturday, he was in bed very bad; I saw him on Sunday about eleven o'clock in bed very bad.</p>
